SIMPLE: squirt
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Squirt
<hw>Squirt</hw> <pr>(skw⟦etil⟧rt)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Squirted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. &
vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Squirting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. LG.
<ets>swirtjen</ets> to squirt, OSw. <ets>sqv⟦aum⟧tta</ets>, E.
<ets>squander</ets>.]</ety> <def>To drive or eject in a stream out of a
narrow pipe or orifice; <as>as, to <ex>squirt</ex> water</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The hard-featured miscreant coolly rolled his tobacco in his
cheek, and <qex>squirted</qex> the juice into the fire grate.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Squirting cucumber</b></col>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <cd>See
<er>Ecballium</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Squirt</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Squirt
<hw>Squirt</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To be thrown out, or
ejected, in a rapid stream, from a narrow orifice; -- said of
liquids.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, to throw out or utter words rapidly; to
prate.</def> <mark>[Low]</mark> <rj><au>L'Estrange.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Squirt</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Squirt
<hw>Squirt</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An instrument out of
which a liquid is ejected in a small stream with force.</def>
<rj><au>Young.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A small, quick stream; a jet.</def>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Hydrodynamics)</fld> <def>The whole system of flow
in the vicinity of a source.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>a youngster.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>a short, overly assertive, or impudent person,
especially when young; -- used in contempt.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Squirter</ent>⟦br⟧
